item.title: Aya Neo Combined Grip
item.description:
This could definitely be improved but it works great for me. I should note that if you care about not scratching up your Aya Neo, I might advise you to not print this as I can't guarantee it won't. I'm personally using a Sopiguard skin on my Neo which is why I feel comfortable using this with my device.

I found that the small bar on the connecting the two sides of the grip was enough structural rigidity while also not really getting in the way of my fingers when using the grip, so I didn't make it higher. It also holds my device so that it doesn't fall out the front if tilted screen-side down. Again, I should note that I do have (an albeit very thin) skin on my device, which could contribute a bit. Adding some adhesive felt on either side of the inside of the grips may help if it is a bit loose for you.

Printed on an Ender 3 Max. This is designed to require no supports, though I did use a brim to ensure adhesion.

item.title: Attachable 1.25'' eyepiece saver for Celestron AVX
item.description: The original eyepiece saver by tirfil is great, but it only sits loosely on the tray of the AVX. So it can fall out easily during transport or at night when one is not careful. I thus just added a thread and a respective nut so that it can be attached tightly to the tray. I also increased the smoothness of the cylinders a bit, for better looks. Like in the original, I provide both the STL and the SCAD file. For using the latter you also need to get the OpenSCAD threading library in version 2.1 (or possibly later) and put its threads.scad file in the same directory as the eyepiecehole-threaded.scad file.
item.author: tisenberg

item.title: Simple First Layer Check - FlashForge Creator Pro
item.description:
Ein einfacher und schneller Erste Schicht Test für den Creator Pro von FlashForge.

Linienbreite Testdruck : 0,8 mm
Höhe : 1 mm
Fläche Testdruck: maximal circa 125mm x 220 mm
Düse Standard Durchmesser: 0,4 mm

Wie immer sollte die Breite der Linie nach der ersten kompletten Schicht überall gleich breit sein. Die Fläche in der Mitte sollte keine zu tiefen Rillen haben und gut haften.

Nach dem Leveling Vorgang den Testdruck starten und eventuell die Bauplatte dementsprechend nachjustieren.

Prinzipell kann der Druck nach der ersten kompletten Schicht abgebrochen werden.

Flashprint: 2 Außenkonturen, (keine Füllung notwendig)
Vorextrusion aktivieren :-)

Viel Spaß beim optimieren !

item.title: cr30 40mm hotend shroud with 5015 blowers
item.description:
I can't seem to find the original hotend case on thingiverse anymore to credit for the remix, so I'm adding it here as well.

cr30_40_5015sMMSred is my current version, I'm using 2x m3 heatset inserts in the thick side brackets and using m3x12mm screws from the back of the hotend carriage into the inserts to mount the shroud to the carriage. I also used 4x m3 heatset inserts to secure the 4020 hotend fan.
